================================================================================
                    LUMEN BOT — HELP & COMMANDS
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
QUICK START
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  1. Invite Lumen to your server (you need "Manage Server" or similar).
  2. Run ,setup (or /setup) and choose the channel where color menus will appear.
  3. Follow the setup wizard:
     • Color set: Basic (~27), Standard (~54), or Full (~108) shades
     • Role restrictions (optional): required role, restricted role, or skip
     • Banners: custom image per family, default banners, or no banners
  4. Confirm and create. Lumen will create the roles and post the reaction menus.
  5. Use ,dashboard (or /dashboard) anytime to edit emojis, banners, embed
     colors, and role restrictions.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
COMMANDS (EVERYONE)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  All of these work as SLASH COMMANDS (e.g. /setup) and as PREFIX COMMANDS
  with the comma prefix (e.g. ,setup). Default prefix: ,

  /setup  (or ,setup)
    • Description: Set up the color role system for this server.
    • Options: channel (required) — the channel where color role messages go.
    • Permissions: You need "Manage Server" (Manage Guild) to run setup.
    • What it does: Starts a wizard. You pick channel, color set size (Basic/
      Standard/Full), optional required/restricted roles, and banners. Then
      Lumen creates the roles and posts one message per color family. Each
      message has an optional banner and a list of shades; users react to get
      that color role.
    • If the server already has a setup: Use /delete (or ,delete) first, then
      run setup again.

  /dashboard  (or ,dashboard)
    • Description: Open the Lumen settings dashboard for this server.
    • Permissions: Manage Server (Manage Guild).
    • What it does: Opens a menu where you can:
      – Role restrictions: Set or clear the "required role" (users must have it
        to use color roles) and "restricted role" (users with it cannot use
        color roles). Use dropdowns or paste role IDs.
      – Emojis: Change the reaction emoji for each color shade (unicode or
        server custom emoji). Pick a family, then a shade, then send the new
        emoji in the channel.
      – Banners: Add, change, or remove the banner image for each color family.
        Send an image, GIF, or image link in the channel when prompted.
      – Embed color: Set the sidebar (accent) color of each color family’s
        embed. Enter a hex color (e.g. #4ECDC4 or 4ECDC4). Leave empty to reset.
      – Close: Dismiss the dashboard message.
    • Tip: Use the "Back" options to change your mind without closing.

  /delete  (or ,delete)
    • Description: Delete the color role setup from this server.
    • Permissions: Manage Server (Manage Guild).
    • What it does: Asks for confirmation. You can choose to remove only the
      config and menu messages, or also delete all color roles created by
      Lumen. If the bot finds orphaned color-role messages (no config), it can
      offer to clean those up too.

  /help  (or ,help)
    • Description: Show all bot commands and details.
    • What it does: Sends you the same help overview (in an embed), including
      quick start, command list, how color roles work, dashboard features, and
      tips. You can run it in the server or in DMs with the bot.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOW COLOR ROLES WORK
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  • Lumen posts one message per color family (e.g. Red, Pink, Blue). Each
    message can have an optional banner image and an embed listing the shades
    (e.g. Blood Red, Crimson, Cherry) with a reaction emoji next to each.

  • Users react with the emoji for the shade they want. The bot adds that
    color role to them. Only one shade per family at a time—reacting to
    another shade in the same family replaces the previous role.

  • If you set a "required role": only users who have that role can get
    color roles; others get a DM explaining they need the role.

  • If you set a "restricted role": users who have that role cannot get
    color roles; they get a DM explaining why.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DASHBOARD FEATURES (SUMMARY)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  • Role restrictions — Who must have a role to use colors / who is blocked.
  • Emojis — Change the reaction emoji for each shade (unicode or server emoji).
  • Banners — Add, change, or remove the image per color family (upload or link).
  • Embed color — Set the sidebar color per family (hex, e.g. #4ECDC4).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIPS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  • Rename or recolor roles in Server Settings → Roles anytime; Lumen keeps
    working. The bot matches roles by ID, not by name.

  • In setup or dashboard, if a role doesn’t appear in the list, paste its
    role ID in the channel (right‑click role → Copy ID, if Developer Mode is on).

  • Use "Back" in setup and dashboard to change your choice without cancelling.

  • For emojis, use only unicode or emojis from the same server. Emojis from
    other servers (e.g. Nitro) may not display correctly for everyone.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BOT OWNER / DEVELOPER COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  These prefix-only commands are for the bot owner and do not respond to
  other users. They are not slash commands.

  ,svrs
    Lists all servers the bot is in (name, ID, member count, owner). Owner-only.

  ,unused-servers
    Shows how many servers have no Lumen setup; optionally makes the bot leave
    those servers after you reply "yes". Owner-only, one-time cleanup style.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PERMISSIONS THE BOT NEEDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  • Manage Roles — to create and assign color roles (and place them correctly
    in the role list if possible).
  • Send Messages, Embed Links, Add Reactions — in the channel where color
    menus are posted, so it can send embeds and add reaction buttons.
  • Read Message History — to handle reactions and dashboard flows.

  When you run setup, Lumen will tell you if it’s missing any of these in the
  chosen channel.

